Access Nonprofit Center is a great resource for Black Families experiencing Developmental Disabilities. Virtual drop-in hours, Parent/Caregiver Support Group, Resource Festivals, Workshops, and more! See flyers for upcoming event dates and contact information. https://t.co/TwdGvXWIbj
We want to hear from our Japanese-speaking community! If you or a loved one in the Torrance area receives Harbor Regional Center services, we want to hear from you! We have limited capacity, please register today to receive meeting details. https://t.co/pnHpeB6OH8
Abilities Expo is coming to the Los Angeles Convention Center from March 15-17. Admission is FREE!!! Learn about the latest products & tech, service dogs, workshops, and much more. See flyer for more information. https://t.co/yCivPOQy3i
Support Strategies for Behavioral Disorders, a 2 week series exclusively for Harbor Regional Center families. Register early and request interpretation if needed. All age groups will be discussed, so bring all your questions. https://t.co/4NlULPOa0h
Childnet Youth & Family Services continúa con su serie de talleres Crianza de los Hijos en Acción mañana de 12 a 1 p. m. en español y de 1:15 a 2:15 p. m. en inglés. Consulte el folleto para obtener información sobre el registro. https://t.co/V0JJHHtlPH
Free Prenatal Yoga & Stretching Class. Join the Community Resource Center of Wilmington every 1st & 3rd Wednesday of the month.   Clase gratuita de yoga prenatal y estiramientos. Únase al Centro de recursos comunitarios de Wilmington cada primer y tercer miércoles del mes. https://t.co/jjh0MgVRPT
Inclusive Sol is an organization that offers a free online support group for parents/caregivers of children with Cerebral Palsy (CP). You can find more information about their support group here: https://t.co/WcI1Ycoa4K They meet every 1st Tuesday of the month, from 5:30 - 7 PM https://t.co/NK41UbCULA
Join us on June 18, 2024 for an informative workshop on self-advocacy. The State Council on Developmental Disabilities (SCDD) will discuss how you can help your loved one become a better self-advocate. Register today! https://t.co/QXRuf6ByJc
You are invited to a Health Fair on June 29 from 10 AM - 2 PM at Greenbelt Park, in Wilmington. See flyer for more information.   Está invitado a una feria de salud el 29 de junio de 10 a. m. a 2 p. m. en Greenbelt Park, en Wilmington. Consulte el folleto para más información. https://t.co/uciXRrcIfW
Our Spring Transition Event will be IN PERSON! We will have a guest speaker discussing employment support and there will be booths with different employment supports for you or your loved to learn more. Please register today and request interpretation if needed. https://t.co/HqBQR7PaEH
Childnet Youth & Family Services continues with their Parenting in Action workshop series tomorrow from 12-1 PM in Spanish, 1:15-2:15 PM in English. Check flyer for registration information. https://t.co/ltZtdKKLRX
¡El Centro Regional Harbor está buscando su opinión sobre nuestras proporciones de casos! Envíe sus ideas de maneras para reducir las proporciones de casos a ratioinput@harborrc.org antes del 21 de junio de 2024. https://t.co/WEKBSHeymF
HRC is excited to announce Cambodian New Year Resource Fair, the first of our cultural celebrations of the year! Individuals served of all ages and their circles of support can interact with staff and find out about the supports available. Join us for food & music! https://t.co/CaSeWoC02N
Abilities Expo llega al Centro de Convenciones de Los Ángeles del 15 al 17 de marzo. La entrada es GRATIS!!! Conozca los últimos productos y tecnología, perros de servicio, talleres y mucho más. Consulte el folleto para obtener más información. https://t.co/B0iEB19LUJ
Acompañenos la próxima semana continuando nuestra serie educativa con TASK. Hablaremos de la comunicación efectiva del IEP y la construcción de relaciones de colaboración. El taller de español es el 25 de julio a las 10AM. Hay interpretación disponible, solicítela al registrarse. https://t.co/3HLmRSjDHS
Acompañe a HRC en su comité asesor de Autodeterminación el 7 de agosto de 6-8 PM vía Zoom. Puede registrarse escaneando el código QR o visitando nuestro sitio web.  https://t.co/d6PdAymB51  Enlace de registro: https://t.co/ern9YHl1PE https://t.co/TJZSt32MPl
Stay connected with Harbor Regional Center by following us on Social Media! Facebook: Harbor Regional Center Instagram: @harborregionalcenter Twitter/X: HarborRC https://t.co/TxHGn4mdTd
Join us for this month’s Saturday Speaker Series (SSS), "Emotion coaching: Strategies for parents to calm those big emotions!" Presented by Kathie Sarles, early childhood specialist 🗓 Saturday, March 23, 24 ⏰ 10AM - 12PM. 💻Zoom Email claudia.sandoval@harborrc.org to register. https://t.co/gSv3UlGgMq
La Sociedad de Autismo de LA (ASLA), en asociación con Phoenix Facilitation,está ofreciendo Capacitación GRATITUA para Facilitadores Independientes de Autodeterminación.  Individuos/Padres de Harbor que deseen convertirse en Facilitadores Independiente y servir a la comunidad,HRC https://t.co/E5WC7pdZKl
Festival de Bienestar de Heart of the City este sábado 6 de abril, frente al California Hospital Medical Center. Habrá comida, zumba, equipos deportivos locales, exámenes de salud y muchas otras actividades. Consulte el folleto para obtener más información. https://t.co/WHPyZ0fexZ
Our next "Coffee with Harbor" will be taking place on September 11. Join Harbor and ICC to help foster change.  Nuestro próximo "Cafecito con Harbor" se llevará a cabo el 11 de septiembre. Únase a Harbor e ICC para ayudar a fomentar el cambio. https://t.co/xQgdNAJnSD https://t.co/v3l7qAZFgr
Heart of the City Wellness Festival, this Saturday, April 6, in front of California Hospital Medical Center. There will be food trucks, zumba, local sports teams, health screenings, and lots of other activities. See flyer for more information. https://t.co/qx36KRAIw6
Harbor Regional Center is seeking your input about our caseload ratios! Please submit you input on ways to reduce caseload rations to ratioinput@harborrc.org by June 21, 2024. https://t.co/rNGwK7JQwA
¡Nuestro evento de transición de primavera será EN PERSONA! Tendremos un orador invitado que hablará sobre el apoyo laboral y tendremos puestos con diferentes apoyos de empleo para usted o su ser querido aprendan más. ¡Es necesario registrarse, ¡confirme su asistencia hoy! https://t.co/A0kvQ5N947
Our next Different Thinkers Different Learners workshop is scheduled for July 2. Learn about Psychoeducational Assessments and be ready to ask questions. This workshop is in Spanish but English interpretation is available with a 5 day notice. Register today! https://t.co/IFkWUn8xfa
Nuestro próximo Su familia Nuestro Enfoque será el 27 de julio de 2024 de 10 a. m. a 12 p. m.  Tendremos oradores invitados que hablarán sobre la intervención conductual y el Programa START. ¡Regístrese hoy! https://t.co/lcn28oMfoZ
Our special education workshop with TASK continues with Age 3 Transitions and the 1st IEP. Diana Huerta will share on everyting you need to know, as well as provide some tips and pointers. Check links for preferred language and register today! https://t.co/Nxsz3WOFS2
Join Carolyn Kordich's Padres LIderes Latinos de Niños con Necesidades Especiales training with Dr. Rosie Zapata. Tuesday, September 10, 2024 from 9AM - 11AM in Wilmington. See flyer for address and RSVP information. https://t.co/74Vj9mxylT
Join us for our next Different Thinkers Different Learners workshop, "The Difference Between ADHD and Autism". Presented by Mariana Leñero and Learning Rights Law Center. Everyone is invited, register today! There will be English interpretation for this workshop. https://t.co/YPAJ6NarYd
Have you ever wondered how to explain a disability that you or a loved one has? Join us for a 2-part series exclusively for Harbor Regional Center families on May 14 & 21. This workshop will be presented in Spanish, please request interpretation at least 5 days prior to event. https://t.co/zif8vtMvxY
